<style>
p.normal {
  border: 2px solid red;
  padding: 5px;
}
p.round1 {
  border: 2px solid red;
  border-radius: 5px;
  padding: 5px;
}
p.round2 {
    border: 5px solid red;
    border-radius: 10px;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<h2>THE BORDER-RADIUS PROPERTY</html>
    <p>This property is used to add 
        rounded borders to an element.
    </p>
    <p class = "normal">This is normal border       
    </p>
    <p class = "round1">This is round border with the border radius of 5px.
    </p>
    <p class = "round2">This is round border with the border radius of 10px.
    </p>
</body>
